start_0ed8288c		"Tonight is a silent night, as I sit in front of my childhood home for the last time. After I return from my trip, the place will have nothing but a Christmas tree and a set table."	game/script.rpy	89		start_0ed8288c
start_81e8b74f		"Tomorrow morning, I will be saying goodbye to a childhood friend who has watched my family and I grow within its walls. I will be leaving for my Aunt's Bed and Breakfast in the countryside, while my mother packs all of our good memories into boxes. At least, the ones that fit. "	game/script.rpy	91		start_81e8b74f
start_0edeb824		"The house I grew up in isn't really a house, but no one ever asks about the two bedroom walk up I grew up in. "	game/script.rpy	94		start_0edeb824
start_bf60cc95		House is a strange word. I don't really like the way it tastes on my tongue. It feels so much more extravagant than what I live in. Why don't people ever ask about my home?	game/script.rpy	97		start_bf60cc95
start_366fde3a		"A house has enough bedrooms for every person living in the place. It has a comfy living space, a backyard and a front porch."	game/script.rpy	100		start_366fde3a
start_8bec53e4		"What it doesn't have is a bedroom so small that the mattress acts as a couch, desk and bed all at once. A house doesn't have four flights of stairs between its occupants and a musty smelling lobby."	game/script.rpy	103		start_8bec53e4
start_294e4cb5		"But, most importantly, a house doesn't have the memory of a deceased loved one lingering in all of the things scattered around the cramped space. Not in the always tidy hamper, or the uncluttered top shelf of the wall unit. Not even in the almost empty refrigerator."	game/script.rpy	106		start_294e4cb5
start_b1e73afe		"My two bedroom walk up certainly isn't a house, but it is a home. A home filled with painful memories that I can no longer stomach. That's why I'm leaving. "	game/script.rpy	110		start_b1e73afe
start_bf376ed7		"Not for good, that would kill my beautiful mother's taped together smile. But, I'll leave until all of the holiday cheer in the streets of New York City is gone. Until I no longer have to watch my mother wrap a gift and label it ""To Craig, from Santa."""	game/script.rpy	114		start_bf376ed7
start_d7b6eb27		We all know that he is going to miss the third Christmas in a row but it will still feel like the very first time we celebrated his favorite holiday without him. 	game/script.rpy	118		start_d7b6eb27
start_cc2282e9		I'll have to look into my mother's hollow eyes as she tears open the finely wrapped paper and exclaim that Craig would appreciate the gift. 	game/script.rpy	121		start_cc2282e9
start_74521e8c		"It's always the same thing too, the sterling silver guardian angel pin that she had given him almost five Christmases ago. The one she and I had spent hours arguing with the postal service on the phone for after they lost the package on route. "	game/script.rpy	125		start_74521e8c
start_3db4c6d7		"This Christmas, my mother will not have to spend the happiest time of year with three spots at the table unclaimed. She has my word. Until that time comes, I need to leave the overtly ""in your face"" holiday cheer that New York City is famous for. "	game/script.rpy	129		start_3db4c6d7
start_fe657b83		"Not because I don't appreciate a large Christmas tree in every well known area or ice skating rinks filled with people chattering excitedly. It's because I just don't know how the city is able to keep moving when, to me and my mother, it feels as if it the world has stopped spinning. "	game/script.rpy	132		start_fe657b83
start_d87851d5		My hand glides over the aluminum mailbox. The same aluminum mailbox that my mother and I would wait anxiously by. Our best memories were when we would finally receive a letter from Craig after months#; we'd both smile and count our blessings. 	game/script.rpy	135		start_d87851d5
start_0632aa0c		"Tonight, there is a different sentiment as I look at the mailbox. Tonight I feel melancholic. But alas, all good things must come to an end eventually. Goodbye, old friend. "	game/script.rpy	138		start_0632aa0c
prologue_de9d1013	ta	"Please have your tickets ready for boarding. This train leaves to Riversone, making local stops along the way."	game/script.rpy	153	TrainLine1	prologue_de9d1013
prologue_632c22d9		"I'm already seated on the train. If living in New York City has taught me anything, it's that behind a crowded train is usually an empty one. Score one for me!"	game/script.rpy	156		prologue_632c22d9
prologue_7a3ee159		"I place my bulky duffel bag on the seat next to me. It's a little tactic I like to call ""uncomfortable silence."" Most people will see my bag and glare at it silently, but they won't tell me to move it. "	game/script.rpy	159		prologue_7a3ee159
prologue_631a7499		"You can't get away with it for the whole ride, but for a few stops it's totally possible. So until some old woman demands I move my stuff, I'm sitting here pretty comfortably. "	game/script.rpy	163		prologue_631a7499
prologue_c00614d6		"Archer Lane's new hit single blasts through the online radio app on my phone. It's catchy, sure, but the high tempo makes me want to chuck my phone at the wall of the train car."	game/script.rpy	167		prologue_c00614d6
prologue_c0a891bf		"Not really feeling the whole, ""Dance with Me"" thing Archer's got going on. Nope, no thanks. Not today, buddy. "	game/script.rpy	171		prologue_c0a891bf
prologue_4f820444		I quickly turn off the app and find my saved music folder. 	game/script.rpy	175		prologue_4f820444
prologue_52692d63		Thomas De Luca is my go to artist. I can feel his raspy voice in the pit of my stomach with each word he sings and it's amazing. 	game/script.rpy	180		prologue_52692d63
prologue_11e0cb8e		He doesn't hide behind autotune like Archer Lane does. Thomas De Luca doesn't need to. I shut my eyes and let his vocals take me to a different place. 	game/script.rpy	183		prologue_11e0cb8e
prologue_80a86c13		"Right now, I'm not on a train to my sister in law's inn to work for the winter. I'm on stage and Thomas De Luca is singing to me. He's holding my hand and letting me know that everything will be okay. "	game/script.rpy	188		prologue_80a86c13
prologue_ae5c4fda		"Even if I know that nothing is okay. Well for one, I can't even stand to look my mother in the eye as she pours an extra cup of hot cocoa in the morning, or sets the table for three people instead of two. How sad is that? I am running away from my own mother!"	game/script.rpy	192		prologue_ae5c4fda
prologue_6b06183d		"On top of that, I have no money. I'm a 22 year old college graduate with a degree in film and a surmounting pile of debt. I had to take out several loans to even afford. All I have to show for my education is one movie and it isn't even that good. I still have no permanent job offers. "	game/script.rpy	195		prologue_6b06183d
prologue_5f80c156		"Thomas De Luca's voice can't magically toss money in my lap or bring the smile back to my mother's face. But, he does help me tune out the world for a few minutes so I can pretend like my problems don't exist. "	game/script.rpy	198		prologue_5f80c156
prologue_496dd894		"When I open my eyes it's because I can feel that the train has stopped moving. I leave my bag next to me, but I drape an arm over it protectively. "	game/script.rpy	204		prologue_496dd894
prologue_075fff8d		A person boards the train and walks casually to the other end of the car. My bag's seat is still secured. 	game/script.rpy	207		prologue_075fff8d
prologue_fc68ae66		I notice that the scenery around me has changed as the train pulls away farther and farther from the big city. There are so many trees and the sunlight isn't hidden by tall buildings.	game/script.rpy	211		prologue_fc68ae66
prologue_51955d86		Riversone might not be so bad after all. Especially if it looks as peaceful as the scene through the train window.	game/script.rpy	214		prologue_51955d86
prologue_2aba1cd7		Riversone is the perfect middle point for travelers heading up north to the textile driven cities or south to the more rural areas. Or so the internet has told me.	game/script.rpy	217		prologue_2aba1cd7
prologue_beef7e4d		"I'm sure I'll meet a lot of interesting people there. Or hey, maybe none at all, which I'm totally cool with too. "	game/script.rpy	220		prologue_beef7e4d
prologue_d3913cc6		"I switch the music off for a second when I notice we're approaching a new station. This one looks much more packed. I give a forlorn look to my bag, which I know I'll have to move onto my lap. It's fine, just a mild inconvenience."	game/script.rpy	225		prologue_d3913cc6
